cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about a convolutional neural network for semantic segmentation of high resolution images under resource constraints. The paper focuses on the efficiency of the network in terms of computation, memory, and power. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new convolutional module, which may fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or multimedia (cs.MM).
